Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @aubergine{1}, then halve lengthways. Cut each half into four long strips,
then widthways into thirds.

Pop the aubergine onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast the aubergine on the top shelf until soft and
golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Coconut Rice ==

Meanwhile, pour the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) into a #medium saucepan{} with a
tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once
boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to
serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Curry ==

While the rice and aubergine cook, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled
and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1/2%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a #large frying pan{} medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the
@desiccated coconut{15%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted,
~{1-2%minutes}.

> Watch it like a hawk as it can burn easily.

Once toasted, transfer to a #small bowl{} and set aside.

Pop your (now empty) #frying pan{} back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g}. Cook until
browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the garlic, @rogan josh curry paste{50%g} and
@North Indian style spice mix{1%sachet}, stir-fry, ~{1%minute}.

Next, stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g},
@sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{150%ml}(for the sauce).

Stir in the chickpeas, then lower the heat and simmer until the sauce has
thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's
> no pink in the middle.

Once the sauce has thickened, season with salt and pepper, then stir in the
roasted aubergine, @mango chutney{40%g} and @butter{20%g}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, stir through the toasted coconut, then share
it out between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon over the chicken, aubergine and chickpea curry and top with a dollop of
@yoghurt{75%g}(Greek style natural) to finish.

Enjoy!